'business'>('normal');\n  const [mediaType, setMediaType] = useState<'images' | 'videos'>('images');\n const [statusFiles, setStatusFiles] = useState<any[]>([]);\n\n  const PATHS = {\n    normal: '/storage/emulated/0/WhatsApp/Media/.Statuses',\n    business: '/storage/emulated/0/WhatsApp Business/Media/.Statuses',\n  };\n\n  const requestPermission = async () => {\n    if (Platform.OS === 'android') {\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    }\n    return false;\n  };\n\n  const loadStatuses = async () => {\n    const hasPermission = await requestPermission();\n    if (!hasPermission) return;\n\n    const statusPath = PATHS[statusType];\n\n    try {\n      const files = await RNFS.readDir(statusPath);\n      const filtered = files.filter(file =>\n        mediaType === 'images'\n          ? file.name.endsWith('.jpg')\n          : file.name.endsWith('.mp4')\n      );\n      setStatusFiles(filtered);\n    } catch (err) {\n      Alert.alert('No statuses found or error accessing path');\n      setStatusFiles([]);\n    }\n  };\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    loadStatuses();\n  }, [statusType, mediaType]);\n\n  const renderItem = ({ item }: any) => (\n    <View style={styles.statusContainer}>\n      {item.name.endsWith('.jpg') ? (\n <Image source={{ uri: 'file://' + item.path }} style={styles.statusImage} />\n      ) : (\n        <View style={[styles.statusImage, { backgroundColor: '#000' }]}>\n          <Text style={{ color: '#fff' }}>🎥</Text>\n        </View>\n      )}\n      <TouchableOpacity style={styles.downloadBtn}>\n        <Icon name=\"arrow-down-circle\" size={26} color=\"green\" />\n      </TouchableOpacity>\n 'react-native-video';\nimport Icon from 'react-native-vector-icons/Ionicons';\nimport { PanGestureHandler, PanGestureHandlerGestureEvent } from 'react-native-gesture-handler';\nimport Orientation from 'react-native-orientation-locker';                              import AsyncStorage from '@react-native-async-storage/async-storage';\n\nconst { width, height } = Dimensions.get('window');\n\nexport default function VideoPlayer({ route, navigation }: any) {\n  const { uri, name, subtitleUri } = route.params || {};\n  const player = useRef<Video>(null);\n  const [paused, setPaused] = useState(false);\n  const [duration, setDuration] = useState(0);\n  const [position, setPosition] = useState(0);\n  const [isFullscreen, setIsFullscreen] = useState(false);\n  const [volume, setVolume] = useState(0.5);\n  const [showTutorial, setShowTutorial] = useState(false);\n\n  // Check AsyncStorage for tutorial\n  useEffect(() => {\n    AsyncStorage.getItem('videoTutorialShown').then(value => {\n      if (!value) setShowTutorial(true);\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  const onLoad = (data: OnLoadData) => setDuration(data.duration);\n\n  const onProgress = (data: OnProgressData) => setPosition(data.currentTime);\n\n  const toggleFullscreen = () => {\n    if (isFullscreen) Orientation.lockToPortrait();\n    else Orientation.lockToLandscape();\n    setIsFullscreen(!isFullscreen);\n  };\n\n  const onGestureEvent = (event: PanGestureHandlerGestureEvent) => {\n    const { translationX, translationY } = event.nativeEvent;\n\n    if (Math.abs(translationY) > Math.abs(translationX)) {\n      // Vertical swipe\n      if (translationY < 0) setVolume(Math.min(volume + 0.05, 1));\n      else if (translationY > 50 && isFullscreen) toggleFullscreen(); // Swipe down → exit fullscreen\n      else setVolume(Math.max(volume - 0.05, 0));\n    } else {\n      // Horizontal swipe → seek                                                              const newPos = translationX > 0 ? Math.min(position + 5, duration) : Math.max(position - 5, 0);\n      setPosition(newPos);                                                                    if (player.current) player.current.seek(newPos);\n    }\n  };                                                                                    \n  const dismissTutorial = async () => {                                                     setShowTutorial(false);\n    await AsyncStorage.setItem('videoTutorialShown', 'true');\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <SafeAreaView style={styles.full}>\n      <StatusBar hidden={isFullscreen} />\n      <View style={styles.header}>\n        <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => navigation.goBack()}>\n          <Icon name=\"arrow-back\" size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        <Text style={styles.headerTitle} numberOfLines={1}>{name || 'Video'}</Text>\n        <View style={{ width: 24 }} />\n      </View>\n\n      <PanGestureHandler onGestureEvent={onGestureEvent}>\n        <View style={styles.playerWrap}>\n          <Video\n            ref={player}\n            source={{ uri }}\n            style={styles.video}\n            resizeMode=\"contain\"\n            paused={paused}\n            volume={volume}\n            onLoad={onLoad}\n            onProgress={onProgress}\n            controls={false}\n            textTracks={\n              subtitleUri\n                ? [\n                    {\n                      title: 'Subs',\n                      language: 'en',\n                      type: TextTrackType.SRT,\n                      uri: subtitleUri,\n                    },\n                  ]\n                : []\n            }\n            selectedTextTrack={\n              subtitleUri ? { type: 'title', value: 'Subs' } : undefined\n            }\n          />\n\n          {/* Overlay controls */}\n          <View style={styles.controls}>\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => setPaused(!paused)} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={paused ? 'play' : 'pause'} size={28} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n\n            <View style={styles.timeWrap}>\n              <Text style={styles.time}>{formatTime(position)}</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.time}> / {formatTime(duration)}</Text>\n            </View>\n\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={toggleFullscreen} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={isFullscreen ? 'contract' : 'expand'} size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Volume display */}\n          <View style={styles.volumeWrap}>\n            <Text style={styles.volumeText}>Vol: {Math.round(volume * 100)}%</Text>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Tutorial Overlay */}\n          {showTutorial && (\n            <View style={styles.tutorialOverlay}>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>🎬 Swipe up/down → Volume</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>⏩ Swipe left/right → Seek</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>🔳 Tap fullscreen → Landscape</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>⬇️ Swipe down → Exit fullscreen</Text>\n              <TouchableOpacity onPress={dismissTutorial}>\n                <Text style={styles.dismissText}>Got it ✅</Text>\n              </TouchableOpacity>\n            </View>\n          )}\n        </View>\n      </PanGestureHandler>\n    </SafeAreaView>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction formatTime(s: number) {\n  if (!s) return '0:00';\n  const mm = Math.floor(s / 60);\n  const ss = Math.floor(s % 60).toString().padStart(2, '0');\n  return `${mm}:${ss}`;\n}\n\nconst styles = StyleSheet.create({\n  full: { flex: 1, backgroundColor: '#000' },\n  header: {\n    height: 56,\n    backgroundColor: requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  try {\n    if (Platform.OS === 'android') {\n      if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n        // Android 13+ (scoped media permissions)\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n        ]);\n        return (\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n        );\n      } else {\n        // Android 12 and below\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n        );\n        return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n      }\n    }\n    return true; // iOS doesn't need manual storage permission\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\nimport RNFS from 'react-native-fs';\nimport { PermissionsAndroid, Platform } from 'react-native';\n\nexport interface VideoFile {\n  name: string;\n  path: string;\n  size: number;\n  modified: number;\n}\n\n// ✅ ask for runtime permission depending on Android version\nasync function requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  if (Platform.OS !== 'android') return true;\n\n  try {\n    if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n      // Android 13+\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n      ]);\n      return Object.values(granted).every(\n        (status) => status === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n      );\n    } else if (Platform.Version >= 30) {\n      // Android 11–12\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    } else {\n      // Android 10 and below\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ scan a folder recursively\nasync function scanFolderForVideos(folderPath: string): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  try {\n    const items = await RNFS.readDir(folderPath);\n    const videos: VideoFile[] = [];\n\n    for (const item of items) {\n      if (item.isDirectory()) {\n        const subVideos = await scanFolderForVideos(item.path);\n        videos.push(...subVideos);\n      } else if (item.isFile() && /\\.(mp4|mkv|avi|mov|flv)$/i.test(item.name)) {\n        videos.push({\n          name: item.name,\n          path: item.path,\n          size: item.size ?? 0,\n          modified: item.mtime ? item.mtime.getTime() : 0,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n    return videos;\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.log('scan error in', folderPath, e);\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ entry point\nexport async function scanAllVideos(): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  const hasPermission = await requestStoragePermission();\n  if (!hasPermission) {\n    console.log('Storage permission not granted');\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  const folders: string[] = [];\n  if (RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath);\n  if (RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath);\n\n  let allVideos: VideoFile[] = [];\n  for (const folder of folders) {\n    const vids = await scanFolderForVideos(folder);\n    allVideos.push(...vids);\n  }\n\n  // sort by modified date desc\n  allVideos.sort((a, b) => b.modified - a.modified);\n  return allVideos;\n}\n~/PlaySoft $ cat android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml\n<manifest xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n 'react-native-orientation-locker';                              import AsyncStorage from '@react-native-async-storage/async-storage';\n\nconst { width, height } = Dimensions.get('window');\n\nexport default function VideoPlayer({ route, navigation }: any) {\n  const { uri, name, subtitleUri } = route.params || {};\n  const player = useRef<Video>(null);\n  const [paused, setPaused] = useState(false);\n  const [duration, setDuration] = useState(0);\n  const [position, setPosition] = useState(0);\n  const [isFullscreen, setIsFullscreen] = useState(false);\n  const [volume, setVolume] = useState(0.5);\n  const [showTutorial, setShowTutorial] = useState(false);\n\n  // Check AsyncStorage for tutorial\n  useEffect(() => {\n    AsyncStorage.getItem('videoTutorialShown').then(value => {\n      if (!value) setShowTutorial(true);\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  const onLoad = (data: OnLoadData) => setDuration(data.duration);\n\n  const onProgress = (data: OnProgressData) => setPosition(data.currentTime);\n\n  const toggleFullscreen = () => {\n    if (isFullscreen) Orientation.lockToPortrait();\n    else Orientation.lockToLandscape();\n    setIsFullscreen(!isFullscreen);\n  };\n\n  const onGestureEvent = (event: PanGestureHandlerGestureEvent) => {\n    const { translationX, translationY } = event.nativeEvent;\n\n    if (Math.abs(translationY) > Math.abs(translationX)) {\n      // Vertical swipe\n      if (translationY < 0) setVolume(Math.min(volume + 0.05, 1));\n      else if (translationY > 50 && isFullscreen) toggleFullscreen(); // Swipe down → exit fullscreen\n      else setVolume(Math.max(volume - 0.05, 0));\n    } else {\n      // Horizontal swipe → seek                                                              const newPos = translationX > 0 ? Math.min(position + 5, duration) : Math.max(position - 5, 0);\n      setPosition(newPos);                                                                    if (player.current) player.current.seek(newPos);\n    }\n  };                                                                                    \n  const dismissTutorial = async () => {                                                     setShowTutorial(false);\n    await AsyncStorage.setItem('videoTutorialShown', 'true');\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <SafeAreaView style={styles.full}>\n      <StatusBar hidden={isFullscreen} />\n      <View style={styles.header}>\n        <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => navigation.goBack()}>\n          <Icon name=\"arrow-back\" size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        <Text style={styles.headerTitle} numberOfLines={1}>{name || 'Video'}</Text>\n        <View style={{ width: 24 }} />\n      </View>\n\n      <PanGestureHandler onGestureEvent={onGestureEvent}>\n        <View style={styles.playerWrap}>\n          <Video\n            ref={player}\n            source={{ uri }}\n            style={styles.video}\n            resizeMode=\"contain\"\n            paused={paused}\n            volume={volume}\n            onLoad={onLoad}\n            onProgress={onProgress}\n            controls={false}\n            textTracks={\n              subtitleUri\n                ? [\n                    {\n                      title: 'Subs',\n                      language: 'en',\n                      type: TextTrackType.SRT,\n                      uri: subtitleUri,\n                    },\n                  ]\n                : []\n            }\n            selectedTextTrack={\n              subtitleUri ? { type: 'title', value: 'Subs' } : undefined\n            }\n          />\n\n          {/* Overlay controls */}\n          <View style={styles.controls}>\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => setPaused(!paused)} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={paused ? 'play' : 'pause'} size={28} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n\n            <View style={styles.timeWrap}>\n              <Text style={styles.time}>{formatTime(position)}</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.time}> / {formatTime(duration)}</Text>\n            </View>\n\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={toggleFullscreen} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={isFullscreen ? 'contract' : 'expand'} size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Volume display */}\n          <View style={styles.volumeWrap}>\n            <Text style={styles.volumeText}>Vol: {Math.round(volume * 100)}%</Text>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Tutorial Overlay */}\n          {showTutorial && (\n            <View a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n      } else if (sortBy === 'size') {\n        arr.sort((a, b) => (b.size || 0) - (a.size || 0));\n      } else {\n        // date\n        arr.sort((a, b) => (b.date || 0) - (a.date || 0));\n      }\n      return arr;\n    },\n    [sortBy]\n  );\n\n  const doScan = useCallback(async () => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    setScanCount(0);\n    const ok = await requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  try {\n    if (Platform.OS === 'android') {\n      if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n        // Android 13+ (scoped media permissions)\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n        ]);\n        return (\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n        );\n      } else {\n        // Android 12 and below\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n        );\n        return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n      }\n    }\n    return true; // iOS doesn't need manual storage permission\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\nimport RNFS from 'react-native-fs';\nimport { PermissionsAndroid, Platform } from 'react-native';\n\nexport interface VideoFile {\n  name: string;\n  path: string;\n  size: number;\n  modified: number;\n}\n\n// ✅ ask for runtime permission depending on Android version\nasync function requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  if (Platform.OS !== 'android') return true;\n\n  try {\n    if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n      // Android 13+\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n      ]);\n      return Object.values(granted).every(\n        (status) => status === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n      );\n    } else if (Platform.Version >= 30) {\n      // Android 11–12\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    } else {\n      // Android 10 and below\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ scan a folder recursively\nasync function scanFolderForVideos(folderPath: string): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  try {\n    const items = await RNFS.readDir(folderPath);\n    const videos: VideoFile[] = [];\n\n    for (const item of items) {\n      if (item.isDirectory()) {\n        const subVideos = await scanFolderForVideos(item.path);\n        videos.push(...subVideos);\n      } else if (item.isFile() && /\\.(mp4|mkv|avi|mov|flv)$/i.test(item.name)) {\n        videos.push({\n          name: item.name,\n          path: item.path,\n          size: item.size ?? 0,\n          modified: item.mtime ? item.mtime.getTime() : 0,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n    return videos;\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.log('scan error in', folderPath, e);\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ entry point\nexport async function scanAllVideos(): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  const hasPermission = await requestStoragePermission();\n  if (!hasPermission) {\n    console.log('Storage permission not granted');\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  const folders: string[] = [];\n  if (RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath);\n  if (RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath);\n\n  let allVideos: VideoFile[] = [];\n  for (const folder of folders) {\n    const vids = await scanFolderForVideos(folder);\n    allVideos.push(...vids);\n  }\n\n  // sort by modified date desc\n  allVideos.sort((a, b) => b.modified - a.modified);\n  return allVideos;\n}\n~/PlaySoft $ cat android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml\n<manifest xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n default function VideoPlayer({ route, navigation }: any) {\n  const { uri, name, subtitleUri } = route.params || {};\n  const player = useRef<Video>(null);\n  const [paused, setPaused] = useState(false);\n  const [duration, setDuration] = useState(0);\n  const [position, setPosition] = useState(0);\n  const [isFullscreen, setIsFullscreen] = useState(false);\n  const [volume, setVolume] = useState(0.5);\n  const [showTutorial, setShowTutorial] = useState(false);\n\n  // Check AsyncStorage for tutorial\n  useEffect(() => {\n    AsyncStorage.getItem('videoTutorialShown').then(value => {\n      if (!value) setShowTutorial(true);\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  const onLoad = (data: OnLoadData) => setDuration(data.duration);\n\n  const onProgress = (data: OnProgressData) => setPosition(data.currentTime);\n\n  const toggleFullscreen = () => {\n    if (isFullscreen) Orientation.lockToPortrait();\n    else Orientation.lockToLandscape();\n    setIsFullscreen(!isFullscreen);\n  };\n\n  const onGestureEvent = (event: PanGestureHandlerGestureEvent) => {\n    const { translationX, translationY } = event.nativeEvent;\n\n    if (Math.abs(translationY) > Math.abs(translationX)) {\n      // Vertical swipe\n      if (translationY < 0) setVolume(Math.min(volume + 0.05, 1));\n      else if (translationY > 50 && isFullscreen) toggleFullscreen(); // Swipe down → exit fullscreen\n      else setVolume(Math.max(volume - 0.05, 0));\n    } else {\n      // Horizontal swipe → seek                                                              const newPos = translationX > 0 ? Math.min(position + 5, duration) : Math.max(position - 5, 0);\n      setPosition(newPos);                                                                    if (player.current) player.current.seek(newPos);\n    }\n  };                                                                                    \n  const dismissTutorial = async () => {                                                     setShowTutorial(false);\n    await AsyncStorage.setItem('videoTutorialShown', 'true');\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <SafeAreaView style={styles.full}>\n      <StatusBar hidden={isFullscreen} />\n      <View style={styles.header}>\n        <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => navigation.goBack()}>\n          <Icon name=\"arrow-back\" size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        <Text style={styles.headerTitle} numberOfLines={1}>{name || 'Video'}</Text>\n        <View style={{ width: 24 }} />\n      </View>\n\n      <PanGestureHandler onGestureEvent={onGestureEvent}>\n        <View style={styles.playerWrap}>\n          <Video\n            ref={player}\n            source={{ uri }}\n            style={styles.video}\n            resizeMode=\"contain\"\n            paused={paused}\n            volume={volume}\n            onLoad={onLoad}\n            onProgress={onProgress}\n            controls={false}\n            textTracks={\n              subtitleUri\n                ? [\n                    {\n                      title: 'Subs',\n                      language: 'en',\n                      type: TextTrackType.SRT,\n                      uri: subtitleUri,\n                    },\n                  ]\n                : []\n            }\n            selectedTextTrack={\n              subtitleUri ? { type: 'title', value: 'Subs' } : undefined\n            }\n          />\n\n          {/* Overlay controls */}\n          <View style={styles.controls}>\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => setPaused(!paused)} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={paused ? 'play' : 'pause'} size={28} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n\n            <View style={styles.timeWrap}>\n              <Text style={styles.time}>{formatTime(position)}</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.time}> / {formatTime(duration)}</Text>\n            </View>\n\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={toggleFullscreen} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={isFullscreen ? 'contract' : 'expand'} size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Volume display */}\n          <View style={styles.volumeWrap}>\n            <Text style={styles.volumeText}>Vol: {Math.round(volume * 100)}%</Text>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Tutorial Overlay */}\n          {showTutorial && (\n            <View style={styles.tutorialOverlay}>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>🎬 Swipe up/down → Volume</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>⏩ Swipe left/right → Seek</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>🔳 Tap fullscreen → Landscape</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>⬇️ Swipe down → Exit fullscreen</Text>\n              <TouchableOpacity onPress={dismissTutorial}>\n                <Text style={styles.dismissText}>Got it ✅</Text>\n              </TouchableOpacity>\n            </View>\n          )}\n        </View>\n      </PanGestureHandler>\n    </SafeAreaView>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction formatTime(s: number) {\n  if (!s) return '0:00';\n  const mm = Math.floor(s / 60);\n  const ss = Math.floor(s % 60).toString().padStart(2, '0');\n  return `${mm}:${ss}`;\n}\n\nconst styles = StyleSheet.create({\n  full: { flex: 1, backgroundColor: '#000' },\n  header: {\n    height: 56,\n    backgroundColor: useState(0);\n\n  const applySort = useCallback(\n    (list: VideoFile[]) => {\n      const arr = [...list];\n      if (sortBy === 'title') {\n        arr.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n      } else if (sortBy === 'size') {\n        arr.sort((a, b) => (b.size || 0) - (a.size || 0));\n      } else {\n        // date\n        arr.sort((a, b) => (b.date || 0) - (a.date || 0));\n      }\n      return arr;\n    },\n    [sortBy]\n  );\n\n  const doScan = useCallback(async () => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    setScanCount(0);\n    const ok = await ensureStoragePermission();\n    if (!ok) {\n      setLoading(false);\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      const list = await scanAllVideos((n) => setScanCount(n));\n      setVideos(applySort(list));\n    } catch (e) {\n      Alert.alert('Scan error', 'Could not scan your storage.');\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  }, [applySort]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    // first open: scan\n    doScan();\n  }, [doScan]);\n\n  // Re-apply sort if user changes option from menu\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (videos.length) setVideos((prev) => applySort(prev));\n  }, [sortBy]);\n\n  const onRefresh = async () => {\n    await doScan();\n  };\n\n  const renderVideo = ({ item }: { item: VideoFile }) => (\n    <TouchableOpacity\n requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  try {\n    if (Platform.OS === 'android') {\n      if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n        // Android 13+ (scoped media permissions)\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n        ]);\n        return (\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n        );\n      } else {\n        // Android 12 and below\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n        );\n        return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n      }\n    }\n    return true; // iOS doesn't need manual storage permission\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\nimport RNFS from 'react-native-fs';\nimport { PermissionsAndroid, Platform } from 'react-native';\n\nexport interface VideoFile {\n  name: string;\n  path: string;\n  size: number;\n  modified: number;\n}\n\n// ✅ ask for runtime permission depending on Android version\nasync function requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  if (Platform.OS !== 'android') return true;\n\n  try {\n    if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n      // Android 13+\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n      ]);\n      return Object.values(granted).every(\n        (status) => status === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n      );\n    } else if (Platform.Version >= 30) {\n      // Android 11–12\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    } else {\n      // Android 10 and below\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ scan a folder recursively\nasync function scanFolderForVideos(folderPath: string): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  try {\n    const items = await RNFS.readDir(folderPath);\n    const videos: VideoFile[] = [];\n\n    for (const item of items) {\n      if (item.isDirectory()) {\n        const subVideos = await scanFolderForVideos(item.path);\n        videos.push(...subVideos);\n      } else if (item.isFile() && /\\.(mp4|mkv|avi|mov|flv)$/i.test(item.name)) {\n        videos.push({\n          name: item.name,\n          path: item.path,\n          size: item.size ?? 0,\n          modified: item.mtime ? item.mtime.getTime() : 0,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n    return videos;\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.log('scan error in', folderPath, e);\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ entry point\nexport async function scanAllVideos(): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  const hasPermission = await requestStoragePermission();\n  if (!hasPermission) {\n    console.log('Storage permission not granted');\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  const folders: string[] = [];\n  if (RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath);\n  if (RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath);\n\n  let allVideos: VideoFile[] = [];\n  for (const folder of folders) {\n    const vids = await scanFolderForVideos(folder);\n    allVideos.push(...vids);\n  }\n\n  // sort by modified date desc\n  allVideos.sort((a, b) => b.modified - a.modified);\n  return allVideos;\n}\n~/PlaySoft $ cat android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml\n<manifest xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n   setStatusFiles([]);\n    }\n  };\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    loadStatuses();\n  }, [statusType, mediaType]);\n\n  const renderItem = ({ item }: any) => (\n    <View style={styles.statusContainer}>\n      {item.name.endsWith('.jpg') ? <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => setStatusType('business')}>\n          <Text style={[styles.bottomText, statusType === 'business' && styles.activeBottom]}>\n            B Status\n          </Text>\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        <Text style={styles.bottomText}>Saved</Text>\n        <Text style={styles.bottomText}>Settings</Text>\n      </View>\n    </View>\n  );\n}\n\nconst styles = 'react-native-video';\nimport Icon from 'react-native-vector-icons/Ionicons';\nimport { PanGestureHandler, PanGestureHandlerGestureEvent } from 'react-native-gesture-handler';\nimport Orientation from 'react-native-orientation-locker';                              import AsyncStorage from '@react-native-async-storage/async-storage';\n\nconst { width, height } = Dimensions.get('window');\n\nexport default function VideoPlayer({ route, navigation }: any) {\n  const { uri, name, subtitleUri } = route.params || {};\n  const player = useRef<Video>(null);\n  const [paused, setPaused] = useState(false);\n  const [duration, setDuration] = useState(0);\n  const [position, setPosition] = useState(0);\n  const [isFullscreen, setIsFullscreen] = useState(false);\n  const [volume, setVolume] = useState(0.5);\n  const [showTutorial, setShowTutorial] = useState(false);\n\n  // Check AsyncStorage for tutorial\n  useEffect(() => {\n    AsyncStorage.getItem('videoTutorialShown').then(value => {\n      if (!value) setShowTutorial(true);\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n  const onLoad = (data: OnLoadData) => setDuration(data.duration);\n\n  const onProgress = (data: OnProgressData) => setPosition(data.currentTime);\n\n  const toggleFullscreen = () => {\n    if (isFullscreen) Orientation.lockToPortrait();\n    else Orientation.lockToLandscape();\n    setIsFullscreen(!isFullscreen);\n  };\n\n  const onGestureEvent = (event: PanGestureHandlerGestureEvent) => {\n    const { translationX, translationY } = event.nativeEvent;\n\n    if (Math.abs(translationY) > Math.abs(translationX)) {\n      // Vertical swipe\n      if (translationY < 0) setVolume(Math.min(volume + 0.05, 1));\n      else if (translationY > 50 && isFullscreen) toggleFullscreen(); // Swipe down → exit fullscreen\n      else setVolume(Math.max(volume - 0.05, 0));\n    } else {\n      // Horizontal swipe → seek                                                              const newPos = translationX > 0 ? Math.min(position + 5, duration) : Math.max(position - 5, 0);\n      setPosition(newPos);                                                                    if (player.current) player.current.seek(newPos);\n    }\n  };                                                                                    \n  const dismissTutorial = async () => {                                                     setShowTutorial(false);\n    await AsyncStorage.setItem('videoTutorialShown', 'true');\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <SafeAreaView style={styles.full}>\n      <StatusBar hidden={isFullscreen} />\n      <View style={styles.header}>\n        <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => navigation.goBack()}>\n          <Icon name=\"arrow-back\" size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        <Text style={styles.headerTitle} numberOfLines={1}>{name || 'Video'}</Text>\n        <View style={{ width: 24 }} />\n      </View>\n\n      <PanGestureHandler onGestureEvent={onGestureEvent}>\n        <View style={styles.playerWrap}>\n          <Video\n            ref={player}\n            source={{ uri }}\n            style={styles.video}\n            resizeMode=\"contain\"\n            paused={paused}\n            volume={volume}\n            onLoad={onLoad}\n            onProgress={onProgress}\n            controls={false}\n            textTracks={\n              subtitleUri\n                ? [\n                    {\n                      title: 'Subs',\n                      language: 'en',\n                      type: TextTrackType.SRT,\n                      uri: subtitleUri,\n                    },\n                  ]\n                : []\n            }\n            selectedTextTrack={\n              subtitleUri ? { type: 'title', value: 'Subs' } : undefined\n            }\n          />\n\n          {/* Overlay controls */}\n          <View style={styles.controls}>\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={() => setPaused(!paused)} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={paused ? 'play' : 'pause'} size={28} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n\n            <View style={styles.timeWrap}>\n              <Text style={styles.time}>{formatTime(position)}</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.time}> / {formatTime(duration)}</Text>\n            </View>\n\n            <TouchableOpacity onPress={toggleFullscreen} style={styles.controlBtn}>\n              <Icon name={isFullscreen ? 'contract' : 'expand'} size={24} color=\"#fff\" />\n            </TouchableOpacity>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Volume display */}\n          <View style={styles.volumeWrap}>\n            <Text style={styles.volumeText}>Vol: {Math.round(volume * 100)}%</Text>\n          </View>\n\n          {/* Tutorial Overlay */}\n          {showTutorial && (\n            <View style={styles.tutorialOverlay}>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>🎬 Swipe up/down → Volume</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>⏩ Swipe left/right → Seek</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>🔳 Tap fullscreen → Landscape</Text>\n              <Text style={styles.tutorialText}>⬇️ Swipe down → Exit fullscreen</Text>\n              <TouchableOpacity onPress={dismissTutorial}>\n                <Text style={styles.dismissText}>Got it ✅</Text>\n              </TouchableOpacity>\n            </View>\n          )}\n        </View>\n      </PanGestureHandler>\n    </SafeAreaView>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction formatTime(s: number) {\n  if (!s) return '0:00';\n  const mm = Math.floor(s / 60);\n  const ss = Math.floor(s % 60).toString().padStart(2, '0');\n  return `${mm}:${ss}`;\n}\n\nconst styles = StyleSheet.create({\n  full: { flex: 1, backgroundColor: '#000' },\n  header: {\n    height: 56,\n    backgroundColor: '#075e54',\n    flexDirection: 'row',\n    alignItems: 'center',\n    justifyContent: 'space-between',\n    paddingHorizontal: 12,\n  },\n  headerTitle: { color: '#fff', fontWeight: '600', marginLeft: 12, flex: 1, textAlign: 'center' },\n  playerWrap: { flex: 1, justifyContent: 'center', alignItems: 'center', backgroundColor: '#000' },\n  video: { width: '100%', height: '100%' },\n  controls: {\n a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n      } else if (sortBy === 'size') {\n        arr.sort((a, b) => (b.size || 0) - (a.size || 0));\n      } else {\n        // date\n        arr.sort((a, b) => (b.date || 0) - (a.date || 0));\n      }\n      return arr;\n    },\n    [sortBy]\n  );\n\n  const doScan = useCallback(async () => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    setScanCount(0);\n    const ok = await => {\n    // first open: scan\n    doScan();\n  }, [doScan]);\n\n  // Re-apply sort if user changes option from menu\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (videos.length) setVideos((prev) => requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  try {\n    if (Platform.OS === 'android') {\n      if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n        // Android 13+ (scoped media permissions)\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n        ]);\n        return (\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED ||\n          granted['android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES'] === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n        );\n      } else {\n        // Android 12 and below\n        const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n          PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n        );\n        return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n      }\n    }\n    return true; // iOS doesn't need manual storage permission\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\nimport RNFS from 'react-native-fs';\nimport { PermissionsAndroid, Platform } from 'react-native';\n\nexport interface VideoFile {\n  name: string;\n  path: string;\n  size: number;\n  modified: number;\n}\n\n// ✅ ask for runtime permission depending on Android version\nasync function requestStoragePermission(): Promise<boolean> {\n  if (Platform.OS !== 'android') return true;\n\n  try {\n    if (Platform.Version >= 33) {\n      // Android 13+\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.requestMultiple([\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO,\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES,\n      ]);\n      return Object.values(granted).every(\n        (status) => status === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED\n      );\n    } else if (Platform.Version >= 30) {\n      // Android 11–12\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    } else {\n      // Android 10 and below\n      const granted = await PermissionsAndroid.request(\n        PermissionsAndroid.PERMISSIONS.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE,\n      );\n      return granted === PermissionsAndroid.RESULTS.GRANTED;\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.warn('Permission error:', err);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ scan a folder recursively\nasync function scanFolderForVideos(folderPath: string): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  try {\n    const items = await RNFS.readDir(folderPath);\n    const videos: VideoFile[] = [];\n\n    for (const item of items) {\n      if (item.isDirectory()) {\n        const subVideos = await scanFolderForVideos(item.path);\n        videos.push(...subVideos);\n      } else if (item.isFile() && /\\.(mp4|mkv|avi|mov|flv)$/i.test(item.name)) {\n        videos.push({\n          name: item.name,\n          path: item.path,\n          size: item.size ?? 0,\n          modified: item.mtime ? item.mtime.getTime() : 0,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n    return videos;\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.log('scan error in', folderPath, e);\n    return [];\n  }\n}\n\n// ✅ entry point\nexport async function scanAllVideos(): Promise<VideoFile[]> {\n  const hasPermission = await requestStoragePermission();\n  if (!hasPermission) {\n    console.log('Storage permission not granted');\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  const folders: string[] = [];\n  if (RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.ExternalStorageDirectoryPath);\n  if (RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath) folders.push(RNFS.DownloadDirectoryPath);\n\n  let allVideos: VideoFile[] = [];\n  for (const folder of folders) {\n    const vids = await scanFolderForVideos(folder);\n    allVideos.push(...vids);\n  }\n\n  // sort by modified date desc\n  allVideos.sort((a, b) => b.modified - a.modified);\n  return allVideos;\n}\n~/PlaySoft $ cat android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml\n<manifest xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO\" />\n    <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES\" />\n\n    <application\n
